            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-4.new-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> red wine vinegar</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>shallot rings</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar </strong>to<strong> </strong>the bowl<strong> </strong>then set aside until later – this is your <strong>quick-pickled shallot</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong> and cook for 3 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add your<strong> curry powder</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Gradually whisk in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[400ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until thickened</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once your sauce has thickened, stir in your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and <strong>mango chutney</strong> – this is your <strong>katsu sauce</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, drain the <strong>quick-pickled shallot</strong>, reserving 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> of the <strong>pickling liquid</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>baby leaf salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and add it to a bowl with the<strong> quick-pickled shallot</strong>, <strong>reserved pickling liquid</strong>, <strong>grated carrot</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1907.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> tofu katsu </strong>over the <strong>katsu sauce </strong>with the <strong>sticky rice </strong>and<strong> salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
